Brachiaria miliiformis

   Authority (Presl.) Chase;
   Family Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
   Synonyms Panicum distachyum, Panicum miliiforme, Panicum
   subquadriparum, Brachiaria supquadripara
   Common names cori grass, green summer grass, two-spiked panic,
   two-finger grass, Thurston grass, milha preta
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 539

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A vigorous, semi-erect grass spreading by stolons.
   USES Used for pasture and hay. Early light grazing a month after
   planting will encourage more rooting of the stolons. GROWING PERIOD
   Summer-growing annual or perennial grass. COMMON NAMES Cori grass,
   Green summer grass, Two-spiked panic, Two-finger grass, Thurston grass.
   FURTHER INF Scientific synonyms: B. miliiformis, Panicum distachyum, P.
   miliiforme, P. subquadriparum. Cori grass is of tropical Asian origin
   from India to the Pacific Islands. It is common on disturbed soil and
   grows well under coconut but should only be sown in coconut stands,
   that are more than 30 years old. Dry matter yields vary between 4-9
   t/ha.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index - In Ecocrop as synonym Brachiaria miliiformis
   Skerman P 1990 pp 260-262 [RAIN, TEXT, FER]
   Mannetje L 1992 pp 67-68 [LIG, TEXT, FER]

